<TITLE> RAB arrests Shibir man in Dhaka for RU murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)  RAB have arrested another activist of Islamic Chhatra Shibir in connection with the killing of Bangladesh Chhatra League worker Faruk Hossain during last month's violence in Rajshahi University. Ikram Hossain was arrested at a mess from Dhamrai's Kamalpur area Monday morning, based on information from fellow Shibir activist Raisul, arrested earlier, RAB's intelligence wing's director Lt Col Ziaul Ahsan said. Hossain, a masters student of RU's Islamic Studies department, has admitted to his involvement in the killing, he said. Ikram gave a detailed description of the Feb 8-9 violence between activists Shibir and BCL, student wings of the fundamental Jamaat-e-Islami and the ruling Awami League respectively. Shibir and BCL clashed at the university on Feb 8. Shibir activists, allegedly instigated by Jamaat, attacked BCL members on campus. Faruk Hossain was killed during the attack. His body was recovered from a manhole next to Shah Makhdum Hall on Feb 9. Scores of Shibir suspects have been rounded up in a countrywide drive in connection with the violence. 
